# CHECKLIST — 05-code-review

**Project**: {{project_name}}
**Generated**: {{current_date}}

> Every applicable item must be checked before submitting a review.

---

## Definition of done

### Understanding
- [ ] PR description is clear and the purpose is understood
- [ ] Scope matches the linked ticket

### Automated checks (on reviewer's machine)
- [ ] `cargo fmt --check` passes on the PR branch
- [ ] `cargo clippy -- -D warnings` passes
- [ ] `cargo test` passes
- [ ] `cargo test --doc` passes

### Correctness
- [ ] Logic does what the description says
- [ ] Edge cases are handled
- [ ] Error paths are correct (no silent failures)
- [ ] No `unwrap()` or `expect()` in non-test code

### Security
- [ ] No new `unsafe` blocks without `// SAFETY:` comments
- [ ] Only approved cryptographic algorithms used (if applicable)
- [ ] No hardcoded secrets or credentials
- [ ] No sensitive data in log statements
- [ ] External inputs validated

### Code quality
- [ ] Functions are short and focused
- [ ] Names are descriptive
- [ ] No unnecessary clones
- [ ] No commented-out code
- [ ] File length ≤ 750 lines

### Tests
- [ ] New functionality has test coverage
- [ ] Error paths are tested
- [ ] No tests removed without explanation

### Review submitted
- [ ] Review submitted with appropriate status (Approve / Comment / Request Changes)
- [ ] All inline comments are clear and actionable

---

## Sign-off

- [ ] This code review is complete and all applicable items above are checked
